        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> 2. Please read CONTRIBUTING.md:\r\n> \r\n> > * NOTE: read the above link before sending improvements to \"runtime files\" (anything in `runtime/`).\r\n> >   - _Vimscript_ files are (mostly) maintained by [Vim], not Nvim.\r\n\r\nI knew that runtime files are maintained by Vim as I have gotten a few upstreamed to Vim and Neovim before, but I wrongly made the assumption that this case was an exception as Vim does not have man.lua\r\n\r\n> 1. Not all shell builtins have man pages. For example, if you remove the 'keywordprg', looking up `shopt` won't work.\r\n\r\nThat is good to know, thank you for taking the time to clarify I really appreciate it!",
